          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Suprachoroidal hemorrhage needs immediate management. Suprachoroidal Hemorrhage Rare dreaded complication of intraocular surgery. Bleeding from long or sho posterior ciliary aery into suprachoroidal space. Risk Factors: Uncontrolled hypeension, advancing age, systemic cardiovascular disease, glaucoma, vitreous loss, increased axial length. Signs Shallowing of AC. Vitreous extrusion. Posterior segments contents may extrude through incision. Tense eyeball. Management Immediate termination of surgery AC is filled with viscoelastic IV mannitol Close the incision Systemic steroids Drainage of suprachoroidal bleed",
