          "explanation": "*Lisch nodules are the most common type of ocular involvement in NF-1. These nodules are melanocytic hamaomas, usually clear yellow to brown that appear as well- defined, dome-shaped elevations projecting from the surface of the iris. Ref: Harrison 18th/e p.2964",
          "hint": "Topic: Miscellaneous"
