          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "\"Cystoid macular edema is a common cause of visual loss in patients with uveitis and may be observed in the setting of severe anterior or intermediate uveitis. Long-standing or recurrent macular edema can cause permanent loss of vision due to cystoid degeneration\".\n- Lange Ophthalmology"
