          "explanation": "Distant Direct Ophthalmoscopy Distance at which DDO performed is 25cm done with direct ophthalmoscope. contains light source viewing window. Normally red glow seen Interpretations Red glow= healthy retina Grey glow = Retinal Detachment No glow = vitreous haemorrhage Black spot in centre = cataract or corneal opacity GOLD STANDARD FOR LOCATING SUBLUXATED LENS: DDO",
