          "explanation": "Gaze fixation stas developing in the first month and is completed in 6 months The macula is fully developed by 4-6 months Fusional reflexes, stereopsis, and accommodation is well developed by 4-6 months Cornea attains normal adult diameter by 2 years of age Lens grows throughout life. Reference : AK Khurana Comprehensive Ophthalmology, 6th edition, pg no. 13",
