          "id": "medmcqa-99a3076a-1980-4668-9174-5b106160200c",
          "text": "A 32 year old patient with history of recurrent headache was sent for fundus evaluation. He was found to be having generalized aerial attenuation with multiple cotton wool spots and flame shaped haemorrhages in both eyes. The most likely cause is:",
