          "explanation": "(Refer: AK Khurana Comprehensive Ophthalmology, 6th edition, pg no. 136)\"Donor corneas are harvested from cadaveric donors within 6 hours after death, sometimes up to 12 hours after death in countries with cold climates\".",
          "hint": "Topic: Ocular trauma "
