          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Symptoms of GCA -such as Headache and tenderness of the temporal aeries and scalp. Jaw claudication, characterized by pain on speaking or chewing, is pathognomonic of GCA,caused by ischaemia of masseter muscle Other symptoms include fever, malaise, anorexia, weight loss, night sweats and joint and muscle pain. GCA is extremely unlikely under 55-60 years. It constitutes an ophthalmic emergency.",
