          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Cattle truck appearance is seen in central retinal aery occlussion. Occurs due to stagnation of blood flow within an aeriole - giving rise to clumping of the blood column within the lumen M/C/C Embolism (Hollenhorst Plaque)",
          "hint": "Topic: Retina"
