          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Ans. D: All of the above Leukocoria is an abnormal white reflection from the retina of the eye. Leukocoria is a medical sign for a number of conditions: Coats disease Congenital cataracts Corneal scarring Melanoma of the ciliary body Norrie disease Ocular toxocariasis Persistence of the tunica vasculosa lentis (PFV/PHPV) Retinoblastoma Retrolental fibroplasia."
