          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Congenital synkinetic ptosis (Marcus Gunn jaw winking ptosis). In this condition there occurs retraction of the ptotic lid with jaw movements i.e., with stimulation of ipsilateral pterygoid muscle. It is due to the mixing of the fibres of 5th and 3rd cranial nerves. Ref:AK Khurana 4thE pg356",
