          "explanation": "Answer- D. EthmoidNasolacrimal CanalThe canal containing the nasolacrimal duct is called the nasolacrirnal canal.It is formed by indentations in the inferior nasal conchae, maxilla and lacrimal bone.It drains to-into the nasal cavity through the anterior poion of the inferior meatus which is between the inferior concha and the floor ofthe nasal cavity."
