          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Direct opthalmoscopy is the most commonly practised method for routine fundus examination. The modern direct opthalmoscope works on the basic principle of glass plate opthalmoscope introduced by von Helmholtz. Characteristics of image formed. In direct opthalmoscopy, the image is erect, viual and about 15 times magnified in emmetropes (more in myopes and less in hypermetropes) Reference : A.K.Khurana; 6th edition; Page no: 587",
