          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "METASTATIC ORBITAL TUMOURS : These involve the orbit by haematogenous spread from a distant primary focus and include the following: * Neuroblastoma -- from adrenals and sympathetic chain. Nephroblastoma --from kidneys. Carcinoma -- from lungs, breast, prostate, thyroid and rectum. Malignant melanoma -- from skin. Ewing's sarcoma --from the bones. Leukaemic infiltration. Commonest tumor to metastasize in children is Neuroblastoma-Raccoon eye sign due to periorbital ecchymosis.",
          "hint": "Topic: Orbit and Adnexa"
