          "explanation": "The most common method of determining IOL power uses a regression formula called 'SRK (Sanders, Retzlaff and Kraff) formula'. The formula is P = A - 2.5L - 0.9K, where: P is the power of IOL, \u0001 A is a constant which is specific for each lens type. \u0001 L is the axial length of the eyeball in mm, which is determined by A-scan ultrasonography. \u0001 K is average corneal curvature, which is determined by keratometry.",
